<br>
The pieces of loot that Axiom Shift claims can be distributed how ever Axiom Shift wants. This includes rewarding people inside and outside the guild for outstanding contributions to raids and the success of Axiom Shift and it's endeavors.<br>
<br>
Just because this option is available to Axiom Shift does not mean we will use it every chance we get. Not only this, we will most definetaly reward our close friends when the chance presents itself and we deem it the right thing to do.<br>
<br>
A Axiom Shift raid will be defined as an event that has 15+ people attending that Axiom Shift has recruited for and leads the day of the event. The minimum amount of time for an event is 3 hours.<br>
<br>
Looking at the formula above Axiom has the option of taking an item once every four hours to distribute how it wishes to.<br>
<br>
Raid time: 1-4 hours Items claimed: 1* (optional)<br>
Raid time: 5-8 hours Items claimed: 1* (optional)<br>
Raid time: 9+  hours Items claimed: 1* (optional<br>
<br>
*as stated above this policy is optional the day of  the event. We may or we may not enforce the policy. <br>
<br>
We will never claim more then 3 pieces of loot at any event we host and lead, no matter the length of the raid.<br>
<br>
If 4 hours passes by and we have not claimed an item, this does not mean during the next four hours we can claim two. The item we have the option to claim only falls into the four hour slot. This will not roll over during the event.<br>
<br>
If Axiom Shift does claim an item to distribute we will announce it to everyone on the raid BEFORE a lotto goes into effect, basically eliminating the need of a lotto for that item.<br>
<br>
This loot policy will go into effect immediately and will have a trial period of 30 days to see how it works.<br>
<br>
Fargus <br>
